RACE.RACE_TEXT: PLEASANTON RACE 1 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 64. Maiden Claiming Purse 12500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COBRE was sent to be prominent in the early running and dueled for pace duties into the turn, set moderate fractions while battling with THECHIEFHASTRICKS through the bend, shook free into upper stretch, drew to a clear lead at the furlong marker and pulled away in the final stages. WOLF'S LIFE lacked early speed, improved position on the turn while saving ground, mounted an inside bid nearing the furlong marker, was not able to keep pace with the winner in the drive, battled with THECHIEFHASTRICKS into deep stretch, drifted out in the final yards to crowd THECHIEFHASTRICKS and just held for the runner-up spot. THECHIEFHASTRICKS broke through the gate prior to the start, was forwardly placed in the early running and pressed the pace while between rivals, kept close attendance to COBRE to the quarter marker, could not match strides into upper stretch and chased to the furlong marker, battled with WOLF'S LIFE in the final furlong, was crowded by that rival in the final yards and just missed for second, while clear of the rest for third. UPDRAFT chased the moderate pace while outside of rivals, made a mild gain while three wide on the turn, lost ground into the stretch and did not offer a late rally. CATCHMENT came a bit in tight leaving the break, took up and was shuffled back in the early running, chased the pace to the turn and advanced inside of rivals nearing the quarter marker, was outrun to mid-stretch and gave way in the late stages. NICKEY BIRD broke alertly and contested the early pace, dropped back nearing the turn, trailed into the stretch run and lacked a late response. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE RUNNING IN DEEP STRETCH AND RULED THAT THERE WOULD BE NO CHANGE TO THE ORDER OF FINISH.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: GROWTH ENGINE bobbled a bit leaving the start but recovered to be forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the moderate pace through the backstretch run, was given his cue along the far turn and confronted BRONZE WARRIOR at the quarter marker, took command into upper stretch, was kept to moderate urging through the final furlong and drew away in the final stages to prevail. BRONZE WARRIOR broke alertly and dictated terms in the early stages, set moderate fractions through the backstretch run, came under pressure from GROWTH ENGINE at the quarter marker, was overtaken by that rival into upper stretch, chased the winner through the final furlong and bested the rest. AWESOME DUDE settled outside of rivals in the early running, was unhurried through the backstretch run, mounted a three wide bid on the far turn and came within aim nearing the quarter marker, could not sustain that bid into the stretch drive and gave way. POUR ON THE COLE settled off of the early pace while not far back, saved all of the ground to the far turn and lacked a response in the stretch drive. MY SUNSHINE stalked the early pace while outside of rivals into the first turn, maintained his position through the backstretch run, dropped back on the far turn, was eased through the stretch and walked off under his own power.

HONEYMOONZ OVER broke alertly, showed speed and dictated terms in the early stages, set a pressured pace on the turn while carving fast fractions, shook free into upper stretch, was kept to task while under firm urging through the lane, was all out in deep stretch and held on to dead heat for the win. RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOM'S REGRET bobbled at the start and was off a step slowly, was steered to the inside and chased the moderate pace into the turn, saved ground while advancing nearing the quarter marker, took command into upper stretch, responded to steady urging at mid-stretch and drew to a clear lead at the furlong pole, was kept to task into the final sixteenth, drew away in the late stages and was hand urged to finish as much the best. RACE.FOOTNOTES: ANNA'S MUSIC stumbled slightly at the break but quickly recovered and gained the early lead in hand, held the field at bay through the turn, responded when asked to go on at the top of the stretch and ran off to a handy win. OH ANGEL hustled for the lead then settled in a tracking spot behind, made an early bid under pressure with three furlongs to run, loomed a threat to the eventual winner at the top of the stretch but could not match strides, was passed by ZOE'S PRIDE inside the furlong grounds but fought back and earned the place. ZOE'S PRIDE was last away from the gate, remained near the rear of the field through the turn, started a rally from the five-sixteenths marker, came in on SOO BROOKLYN at the top of the stretch then ran on well down the lane, briefly gained second but was outgamed in the final yards. SOO BROOKLYN broke inward at the start and mutually bumped with BOBBY'S GENIE, then was bumped again by that one a few strides later, raced mid-pack and in the three to four path down the backstretch, angled to the inside for the run into the stretch, was bumped by ZOE'S PRIDE at the head of the stretch but kept on and finished with some interest. BOBBY'S GENIE broke out slightly and made contact with SOO BROOKLYN then continued to lean out and bumped that one lightly once again, moved quickly up the rail to challenge for the early lead while the rider was doing his best to keep a straight course, loomed a threat through the turn then weakened from the three-sixteenths pole. RAY TAYLORS RUMBLE broke with the pack but was outrun early, fell far back before the turn, stayed in the four or five path through the turn and into the stretch and was never a factor.
